posts.title: A final Sunday night
posts.content:
I do not care if you sit in the reddest county in South Dakota, get out there and vote. If you have already voted then crawl to the nearest house and make sure you get all your fed up friends and families to vote. The cost of not doing everything you can is too much. Vote; We live in a world where every single one of us has a voice. And that voice is our vote. It's our chance to stand up, to speak out. This is the future I believe in. These are the values I stand for.

But let’s be real. Sometimes, it can feel like one vote doesn't matter, that the system is too big or that things won’t change, that there is fraud and your vote wont count. And that's exactly what those who want to maintain the status quo rely on. They rely on us staying quiet. They rely on us sitting this one out. But here’s the truth: every vote does count. Your vote counts. Your vote could be the one that tips the scales, that breaks the tie, that brings a new idea to life or safeguards a community.

Remember, we stand on the shoulders of giants. We stand against a tyrannical government that needlessly kills our pet squirrels. We stand against a government that takes our jobs when we don't poison ourselves. We stand for American values where our laws matter. Where we wont be replaced because liberals need someone to sow their crops and clean their toilets. We stand together because we may be garbage, deplorable or Nazis to some, but treasure to others. We stand for Trump, he has given fame and fortune for us. We vote to honor those who fought tirelessly, who sacrificed their lives, who marched, who spoke up so we could stand here with this right. Voting is a legacy. It’s a privilege. And it’s a responsibility.

So, make a plan. Find your polling place. Bring a friend, bring your family, bring your passion. And when you step into that booth or fill out that ballot, know that you are a part of something bigger than yourself. Know that you are a force for change.

Vote like your future depends on it—because it does. Vote like your voice matters—because it does. And when you vote, know that you’re not just shaping the present; you’re building the future and preserving the country.

Wake up the last hope

Keep pushing ahead

The best is yet to come

Knife party

We will have our homes again

VOTE, CRAWL THROUGH GLASS AND VOTE!!!! NOTHING ELSE MATTERS
